The following is a list of
companies that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and
Irish markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last market close.  Futures on the FTSE 100 Index climbed 0.9 percent to 5,060
as of 7:53 a.m. in  London . The gauge lost 4.7 percent to
5,041.61 yesterday.  Collins Stewart Hawkpoint Plc (CSHP LN): The company said
its securities unit is unlikely to recoup the effect of recent
poor trading performance in the current financial year. Overall,
the group has traded less profitably than last year, the company
said. The shares rose 1.5 percent to 69 pence.  Daily Mail & General Trust Plc (DMGO)  :  Daily Mail  was
downgraded to “equal weight” from “over weight” at Barclays
Plc. The shares slid 5.3 percent to 346.5 pence.  Smith & Nephew Plc (SN/)  : The shares were downgraded to
“sell” from “buy” at Citigroup Inc. The stock lost 3.3
percent to 571 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adam Haigh in London at 
 ahaigh1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
